Defendant Miguel Angel Aponte in court with attorney Jonathan Carver Smith.  Hanna R. Kolberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
AS TO COUNT  1- 
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 7 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 30 MONTHS with the following conditions:
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Court ordered 6 MONTHS condition time at the House of Corrections, without good time credit, with release for work and school only, and the Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoringm, to begin forthwith. 
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety, no alcohol.
- No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid 
  prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
  and successfully complete recommended treatment
  including drug and alcohol testing. 
- No possession of any alcohol.
- No use or possession of any illegal drug without a valid prescription. 
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia, for personal use or use associated with delivering, manufacturing or distributing. 
- No possession of any weapons, firearms, ammunition or holster. 
-Maintain full time work and/or school.
- Successfully complete a Parenting class.
- Court ordered Defendant to comply with all child support court orders. 
- Court ordered Defendant to comply with paying Department of Correction Supervision fees. 
- Provide DNA sample if not already provided. 
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including
  the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. 
  Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due
  or civil judgment to be entered. 
- Court prohibits contact with Edgar R. (D.O.B.7-30-1987) during confinement and during Extended Supervision.


Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.

Court advises the Defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount actually served may be extended, and that the Defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The Defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to extended supervision, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the Defendant being returned to prison.
